New Features and Important Changes in GammaLib 1.0.1

Author(s) : Juergen Knoedlseder

22 January 2016


1. Introduction
---------------
This document briefly summarizes module by module the most important changes
made since the last release of GammaLib.


2. Public interface modifications
---------------------------------
None


3. Configuration
-----------------
If GammaLib is compiled on Mavericks (Mac OS X 10.9) or newer but Python has been
compiled for an earlier deployment target, a compatibility issue arises due to the
way how class names are mangled by the compiler. This is now automatically detected
and fixed, which should solve some compatibility issues that have been encountered
by user using the Anaconda package on Mac OS X.


